.TH "cap_task_fix_setuid" 9 "cap_task_fix_setuid" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cap_task_fix_setuid \- Fix up the results of setuid() call
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cap_task_fix_setuid
.BI "(struct cred *new "  ","
.BI "const struct cred *old "  ","
.BI "int flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "new" 12
The proposed credentials
.IP "old" 12
The current task's current credentials
.IP "flags" 12
Indications of what has changed
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Fix up the results of \fBsetuid\fP call before the credential changes are
actually applied, returning 0 to grant the changes, -ve to deny them.
